		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />21.47727Mhz clock, 5V, 5 pin controller connections, rom chip has 55-57 connections (didn't count too hard), also the interviews on the net I've seen with people who supposedly worked on it talking about the pluses of porting rather than making a custom chip. Not too solid, but it's pointing in that direction <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
